### File permission

4 = Read (r)
2 = Write (w)
1 = Execute (x)
4 + 2 + 1 = 7 (Read, Write, Execute)


chmod 755 script.sh

Owner   → read write execute
Group   → read execute
Others  → read execute

4. Creating your own group
If you want to create a new group for a specific project:
Create the group: sudo groupadd project_alpha
Add a user to it: sudo usermod -aG project_alpha username

chmod 664 file: Owner/Group can read/write; Others can only read.

If the group doesn't already own the file, use chgrp - sudo chgrp groupname filename

