### Docker

install - sudo apt install docker.io -y

start -
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl status docker

test -
docker run hello-world


Aviod sudo everytime

sudo usermod -aG docker $USER -  run docker as normal user 



Pull an image - docker pull nginx

see local images - docker images

Run a container - docker run nginx

see running containers - docker ps

see all including stopped containers - docker ps -a

stop a container - docker stop CONTAINER_ID

remove container - docker rm CONTAINER_ID

runs in background - docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx

What this means:

-d = run in background
-p 8080:80 = host port 8080 forwards to container port 80
nginx = image name
your VM port 8080  →  container port 80

docker ps - you should see a running container http://localhost:8080


see container logs - docker logs CONTAINER_ID


